%description:

Protocol Test Framework -- example opp_test wrapper (negative / violation detection).

Demonstrates that the framework *catches* a protocol violation. The `tcp_handshake_seq_bad`
program asserts a wrong relationship for the SYN+ACK host1 receives (it expects the ack
number to be ISN+2 instead of ISN+1), so the matcher must NOT find a matching event and the
run ends in a FAIL verdict. This `.test` passes precisely because the framework reports the
failure -- i.e. it confirms the matcher rejects an incorrect trace.

%extraargs: -l ../lib/libprotocoltest.so -n ../../../src;../lib

%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = ProtocolTestDemo
sim-time-limit = 1s
seed-set = 0

*.host1.numApps = 1
*.host1.app[0].typename = "TcpSessionApp"
*.host1.app[0].connectAddress = "host2"
*.host1.app[0].connectPort = 1000
*.host1.app[0].tOpen = 0.1s
*.host1.app[0].tSend = 0.2s
*.host1.app[0].sendBytes = 100B
*.host1.app[0].tClose = 2s
*.host2.numApps = 1
*.host2.app[0].typename = "TcpEchoApp"
*.host2.app[0].localPort = 1000

*.tester.testName = "tcp_handshake_seq_bad"

%contains: stdout
PROTOCOLTEST tcp_handshake_seq_bad: FAIL
